com.google.mu.function

Interface BiComparator<K,V>

  • Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface BiComparator<K,V>
    Similar to Comparator, but compares between two pairs of objects.

    Note: For ease of reference, this interface uses 'key' and 'value' to refer to the two parts of a pair respectively. However, both 'key' and 'value' can be of any type, or null. There is no implication that the 'key' or 'value' must implement Object.equals(java.lang.Object). You may equivalently read them as 'left' and 'right', or 'night' and 'day'.

    Since:
    4.7
